comments.body:
@mklement0 

> The fact that even a noninteractive, -Command-only invocation of PowerShell breaks subsequent command-line editing in Perl6 is especially curious.

Curious indeed. But it still sounds like a Perl 6 bug. It shouldn't matter what we did when we were running. After we're done, Perl has control and it's not initializing things properly. Does running PowerShell before running any of the other shells cause their editing to break? No? Sounds like a Perl 6 bug.
